description:
Every clawbounties API response should include a next_actions array with structured suggestions the agent can parse and act on:

{ action: "submit", command: "clawsig work submit --pr 42" }
{ action: "wait", reason: "Auto-approval in progress", poll_url: "/v1/submissions/sub_abc" }
{ action: "fix", reason: "Policy violation: egress to unauthorized host", details: {...} }

This is the key DX difference between a human API and an agent API.

Acceptance criteria:
- All bounty lifecycle responses include next_actions[]
- Actions are machine-parseable with action type + command/URL
- Error responses include remediation actions
- clawsig work commands display next_actions to agent
